### v7.0 — LoTW Integration & Bandmap Improvements

**LoTW (Logbook of the World) Integration**

- Secure login from the web interface — credentials never stored on disk
- Full log import: all uploaded QSOs + confirmed QSLs
- DXCC resolution via `cty.dat` (no dependency on optional ADIF field)
- Statistics: total QSOs, confirmed QSLs, confirmed DXCC per band (visual bar chart)
- **In HF and VHF spot tables**: red background + NEW badge = DXCC never worked / green + ✓ = already confirmed
- **★ NEW DXCC button** in HF and VHF panels to filter new DXCC only
- **In the watchlist**: NEW DXCC or ✓ LoTW badge on each callsign
- Loading spinner during synchronization (30–60s for a large log)

**Bandmap**

- Zoom increased to 100× for busy bands (e.g. 20m)
- Pin label color by mode: CW (green), SSB (blue), FT8 (purple), FT4 (pink), FT2 (mauve), RTTY (orange), PSK31 (yellow), JT65 (cyan)
- Mode legend displayed in the controls bar
- Frequency axis: only real amateur radio band edges shown
- Mouse pan (click + drag) available even at zoom 1×
- All settings persisted via localStorage

